</ul></div></nav><div class="site-inner"><div class="content-sidebar-wrap"> <main class="content"><div class="breadcrumb">You are here: <span class="breadcrumb-link-wrap"><a class="breadcrumb-link" href="https://www.manusmenu.com/"><span class="breadcrumb-link-text-wrap">Home</span></a><meta ></span> <span aria-label="breadcrumb separator">/</span> <span class="breadcrumb-link-wrap"><a class="breadcrumb-link" href="https://www.manusmenu.com/category/recipes"><span class="breadcrumb-link-text-wrap">Recipes</span></a><meta ></span> <span aria-label="breadcrumb separator">/</span> <span class="breadcrumb-link-wrap"><a class="breadcrumb-link" href="https://www.manusmenu.com/category/recipes/candy-2"><span class="breadcrumb-link-text-wrap">Candy</span></a><meta ></span> <span aria-label="breadcrumb separator">/</span> Honey Hard Candy</div><article class="post-24229 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-candy-2 category-diy category-italian tag-candy tag-diy tag-honey tag-italian tag-sugar tag-sweets entry" aria-label="Honey Hard Candy"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title">Honey Hard Candy</h1>
<p class="entry-meta"><time class="entry-time">March 7, 2016</time> Last updated on <time class="entry-modified-time">January 16, 2026</time> By <span class="entry-author"><a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/author/admin" class="entry-author-link" rel="author"><span class="entry-author-name">Manu</span></a></span> <span class="entry-comments-link"><a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy#comments">34 Comments</a></span></p></header><div class="entry-content"><div class="wprm-recipe-snippets" style="text-align: left;"><a href="#wprm-recipe-container-28962" data-recipe="28962" style="" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal">Jump to Recipe</a> <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/wprm_print/honey-hard-candy" style="" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe-id="28962" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Print Recipe</a></div>


<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>Need a<em> sweet treat</em> that’s both <em>homemade </em>and soothing? <strong>Honey Hard Candy</strong> is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a <em>thoughtful gift for any occasion</em>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="667" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=40143" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-wrapped-candies.webp" alt="Wrapped honey hard candies on parchment paper." class="wp-image-40143" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-wrapped-candies.webp 1000w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-wrapped-candies-300x200.webp 300w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-wrapped-candies-768x512.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></figure>



<p>Have you ever made your own candy? I’d made caramel and sugar decorations before, like the ones for my <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/frozen-cake">Frozen Cake</a>, and even a few <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/rock-candy-lollipops">Rock Candy Lollipops</a>, but never flavoured hard candy. The idea came to me one cool morning when I had a sore throat and started craving the honey sweets I used to buy back home.</p>
</div></div>



<p>I took out my saucepan and thermometer and made a batch of homemade honey hard candy. They’re simple and comforting for those days when you need something soothing. I like keeping a few honey candies in a jar for when someone catches a cold, they always come in handy.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-honey-hard-candy"><strong>What is Honey Hard Candy?</strong></h2>


<p>Honey Hard Candy (or honey lozenges) is an old-fashioned treat made by cooking sugar, water, lemon juice, and honey until the mixture reaches the <a href="https://www.exploratorium.edu/explore/cooking/candy-making-stages" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">hard crack stage</a> (about 146°C–155°C or 295°F–310°F). Once cooled, it hardens into golden, glass-like drops that slowly melt in your mouth.</p>



<p>These honey candies aren’t only delicious but also help soothe a sore throat naturally.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-this-honey-candy-is-worth-making">Why This Honey Candy Is Worth Making</h2>


<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Made with real ingredients and free from preservatives or additives.</li>



<li>Naturally soothing for sore throats and dry coughs, especially on cooler days.</li>



<li>Makes a thoughtful homemade gift for friends and family during the holidays</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="key-ingredients-for-homemade-honey-hard-candy">Key Ingredients for Homemade Honey Hard Candy</h2>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img decoding="async" width="718" height="540" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=41571" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-sugar-water-ingredients-for-caramel.webp" alt="Honey, sugar, water, and lemon juice ingredients prepared for caramel mixture." class="wp-image-41571" style="width:824px;height:auto" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-sugar-water-ingredients-for-caramel.webp 718w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-sugar-water-ingredients-for-caramel-300x226.webp 300w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-sugar-water-ingredients-for-caramel-500x375.webp 500w" sizes="(max-width: 718px) 100vw, 718px" /></figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sugar">Sugar</h3>


<p>Creates the base of the candy and gives it a crisp texture. It balances the sweetness of the honey and enhances the light citrus flavour from the lemon juice.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="honey">Honey</h3>


<p>Adds natural sweetness and a mild floral taste that makes the candy smooth and pleasant. Use pure, light-coloured honey for a clear golden colour.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="lemon-juice">Lemon Juice</h3>


<p>Provides a light tang that keeps the candy from tasting overly sweet. It also complements the flavour of the honey.</p>



<p><em>Find the complete list with measurements in the recipe card below.</em></p>
</div></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-make-honey-hard-candy">How to Make Honey Hard Candy</h2>


<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p><strong>Step 1: </strong>In a pot, mix together the sugar, water, and lemon juice and put it on the fire on a medium flame.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="716" height="540" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=41574" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sugar-syrup-starting-to-melt-in-saucepan.webp" alt="Sugar syrup beginning to dissolve and melt in a metal saucepan." class="wp-image-41574" style="width:824px;height:auto" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sugar-syrup-starting-to-melt-in-saucepan.webp 716w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sugar-syrup-starting-to-melt-in-saucepan-300x226.webp 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<p><strong>Step 2: </strong>When the mixture boils, decrease the flame to low and stir in the honey.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Caramelise the mixture and cook it until it reaches the hard crack stage (146°C–155°C / 295°F–310°F) on a candy thermometer.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="717" height="540" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=41573" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/caramel-mixture-cooking-to-hard-crack-stage.webp" alt="Caramel mixture cooking to the hard-crack stage with thermometer temperature shown." class="wp-image-41573" style="width:826px;height:auto" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/caramel-mixture-cooking-to-hard-crack-stage.webp 717w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/caramel-mixture-cooking-to-hard-crack-stage-300x226.webp 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Pour the hot caramel carefully into silicone moulds while it’s still liquid.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="718" height="540" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=41575" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/black-caramel-poured-into-moulds.webp" alt="Dark caramel poured into a silicone mould to set into glossy discs." class="wp-image-41575" style="width:824px" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/black-caramel-poured-into-moulds.webp 718w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/black-caramel-poured-into-moulds-300x226.webp 300w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/black-caramel-poured-into-moulds-500x375.webp 500w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 718px) 100vw, 718px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p><strong>Step 5: </strong>Let the candy cool and harden completely at room temperature before unmoulding.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="667" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=40144" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-in-moulds.webp" alt="Homemade honey hard candies cooling in silicone moulds." class="wp-image-40144" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-in-moulds.webp 1000w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-in-moulds-300x200.webp 300w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/honey-hard-candy-in-moulds-768x512.webp 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></h2>


<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759762711780"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How can I tell when honey hard candy is done without a thermometer?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Drop a small amount of the syrup into cold water. If it hardens into brittle threads that snap easily, it’s ready. If it stays soft or sticky, return it to the heat and cook a little more.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759762712864"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I add food colouring to my Honey Hard Candy recipe?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, you can. Use a few drops of gel or liquid food colouring once the syrup reaches the correct temperature. Light-coloured honey works best if you want the colours to show clearly.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759762758835"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What’s the best way to clean the pot after making candy?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Fill the pot with hot water and let it sit for a few minutes. The hardened sugar will dissolve easily, and you can then wash it as usual. Avoid scraping while it’s still hot to prevent damage.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1759762776224"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I use brown sugar instead of white sugar?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, but the candy will turn darker and have a stronger caramel flavour. Brown sugar contains molasses, which changes both colour and taste slightly.</p> </div> </div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="extra-help-from-the-kitchen">Extra Help from the Kitchen</h2>


<p><strong>Use Baking Paper </strong>– If you don’t have silicone moulds, drop small spoonfuls of the syrup onto parchment paper. They’ll cool into thin, round candies. Be careful not to touch the hot syrup.</p>



<p><strong>Keep the Heat Low</strong> – Honey burns fast, so once it starts boiling, lower the flame to maintain a steady temperature.</p>



<p><strong>Avoid Stirring After Boiling</strong> – Stop stirring once the syrup starts to bubble so the sugar does not crystallise.</p>
</div></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="variations-and-twists">Variations and Twists</h2>


<p><strong>Ginger Honey Hard Candy</strong> – Add a teaspoon of finely grated fresh ginger to the syrup for a warm, slightly spicy flavour.</p>



<p><strong>Use Light-Coloured Honey </strong>– Light honey caramelises into a golden colour, while dark honey creates a deeper amber shade and stronger flavour.</p>



<p><strong>Turn Them into Lollies </strong>– Add sticks to moulds before pouring for easy homemade honey lollies.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="storage-and-shelf-life">Storage and Shelf Life</h2>


<p>To store the Honey Hard Candy, wrap each piece individually in wax or baking paper to prevent sticking. Keep them in an airtight container or Ziploc bag at room temperature for up to 2 months.</p>



<p>If you live in a hot or humid area, store them in the refrigerator so they stay firm and dry. Avoid freezing, as condensation can make them sticky once thawed.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="other-homemade-candies-to-try-next">Other Homemade Candies to Try Next</h2>


<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="soft-vanilla-and-pink-salt-caramels">Soft Vanilla and Pink Salt Caramels</h3>


<p><em>Sweet and chewy, <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/soft-vanilla-pink-salt-caramels">Soft Vanilla and Pink Salt Caramels</a> are one of my favourite treats to make at home. They’re smooth, buttery, and a little indulgent.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="667" height="1000" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=40145" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/soft-vanilla-pink-salt-caramels.webp" alt="Soft vanilla caramels sprinkled with pink salt and wrapped in paper." class="wp-image-40145" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/soft-vanilla-pink-salt-caramels.webp 667w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/soft-vanilla-pink-salt-caramels-200x300.webp 200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="homemade-jelly-candies">Homemade Jelly Candies</h3>


<p><em>If you like fruity sweets, <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/homemade-jelly-candies">Homemade Jelly Candies</a> are fun to make and look beautiful when wrapped in sugar crystals.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="534" height="800" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=40146" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-jelly-candies-lemon-orange.webp" alt="Homemade lemon and orange jelly candies coated in sugar." class="wp-image-40146" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-jelly-candies-lemon-orange.webp 534w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/homemade-jelly-candies-lemon-orange-200x300.webp 200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 534px) 100vw, 534px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="rock-candy-lollipops">Rock Candy Lollipops</h3>


<p><em>These <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/rock-candy-lollipops">Rock Candy Lollipops</a> are bright, colourful, and perfect for parties or gifts. They’re also a fun science project for kids.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="667" height="1000" data-pin-url="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy?tp_image_id=40147" data-pin-media="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Honey-Hard-Candy-Recipe-Pin.webp" data-pin-description="Need a sweet treat that’s both homemade and soothing? Honey Hard Candy is easy to make, looks lovely, and makes a thoughtful gift for any occasion." data-pin-title="Honey Hard Candy Recipe" data-pin-id="" src="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rock-candy-lollipops-blue-sticks.webp" alt="Blue rock candy lollipops in a small glass jar." class="wp-image-40147" srcset="https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rock-candy-lollipops-blue-sticks.webp 667w, https://www.manusmenu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rock-candy-lollipops-blue-sticks-200x300.webp 200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="honeycomb">Honeycomb</h3>


<p><em>Crisp and airy, <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/honeycomb">Honeycomb</a> is another easy <a href="https://www.manusmenu.com/category/recipes/candy-2">candy recipe</a> you’ll love. It adds a little crunch to desserts or is great on its own.</em></p>



