		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img data-pin-nopin="nopin" alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4a41527f0a8d01ea10bb8b59fb0e98847060aa3cf70cddb804139e4a333eae62?s=48&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4a41527f0a8d01ea10bb8b59fb0e98847060aa3cf70cddb804139e4a333eae62?s=96&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/><span class="comment-author-name"><a href="https://www.manusmenu.com" class="comment-author-link" rel="external nofollow">Manu</a></span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time"><a class="comment-time-link" href="https://www.manusmenu.com/honey-hard-candy#comment-732106">June 8, 2020 at 6:38 pm</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Hi Sarah. You can simply drop some of the melted candy on a piece of parchment paper. You will get thin lollypop-like candies. Be careful not to get burnt!</p>
